{
    "type": "section",
    "id": "blog-sidebar",
    "layout": "row",
    "settings": {
        "bg": "#0a0a14",
        "padding": "60px 24px",
        "maxWidth": "1100px",
        "gap": "48px",
        "columns": 2
    },
    "blocks": [
        {
            "type": "card",
            "id": "blog-content-col",
            "settings": {
                "bg": "transparent",
                "padding": "0",
                "border": "none"
            },
            "children": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "id": "bc-cat",
                    "text": "Design",
                    "settings": {
                        "color": "#6366f1",
                        "fontSize": "10px",
                        "fontWeight": "700",
                        "letterSpacing": "0.14em",
                        "textTransform": "uppercase",
                        "marginBottom": "12px"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "id": "bc-title",
                    "text": "How to build a design system from scratch",
                    "tag": "h1",
                    "settings": {
                        "color": "#e8e8f0",
                        "fontSize": "32px",
                        "fontWeight": "700",
                        "lineHeight": "1.25",
                        "marginBottom": "10px"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "id": "bc-meta",
                    "text": "February 20, 2026  |  Crissy Deutsch  |  8 min read",
                    "settings": {
                        "color": "#5555a0",
                        "fontSize": "11px",
                        "letterSpacing": "0.04em",
                        "marginBottom": "28px"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "id": "bc-intro",
                    "text": "Every design system starts with the same problem: inconsistency. Colors drift. Spacing values multiply. Component names diverge across files. The system is the solution, but only if you build it deliberately.",
                    "settings": {
                        "color": "#c7c7f0",
                        "fontSize": "16px",
                        "lineHeight": "1.75",
                        "marginBottom": "20px"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "id": "bc-body",
                    "text": "Tokens are the primitive values your system is built on: color, spacing, typography, radius, shadow. When you define those first, every component that references them stays consistent automatically. Change a token and everything composed from it updates.",
                    "settings": {
                        "color": "#8888a0",
                        "fontSize": "15px",
                        "lineHeight": "1.75"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
